comments.message:
Mentioning 'Resolves' updates the JIRA ticket.
So here you just updated LE-123 :p

Here 'Resolves:' should be FWATE-900

It seems that the convention that you have on FWATE is a bit different.
Like:
  [FWATE-286][FWATE-371] Add USB2.0 current consumption test cases + Macro change

If possible, it would be best if you can switch to the:

  Add USB2.0 current consumption test cases + Macro change  

  Resolves: FWATE-286 FWATE-371
  Related: FWATE-123

Note that Related is optional, and the Resolves part is required by default but could be set as optional.

This is the convention that we have for Legato and most other projects with few exceptions such as mdm9xxx projects, kernel, ...

If you prefer to stick with your convention, you can create a FARM ticket and we can adapt the 'commit checker' for your convention (needs to be explicitly defined in the ticket).

ohhhhh... boy. it actually updates the ticket. Sorry for spamming Le-123 watchers..  
I just updated it to 'Resolves: FWATE-286 FWATE-371' but the checker is still complaining.
Oh ... it might be because the user CARMD-EV-LXCIM_sa (which is behind the commit checker) can't access these tickets.
